00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:02,038
JavaScript supports closures

2
00:00:02,288 --> 00:00:07,100
a powerful attribute that allows for the creation of private variables and functions

3
00:00:07,475 --> 00:00:14,125
Closures provide the capability to retain scope access even after a function has completed execution

4
00:00:14,512 --> 00:00:18,887
This feature is essential for creating modules and reducing dependency

5
00:00:19,312 --> 00:00:22,325
thereby promoting private state and encapsulation

